k         = y\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n\n| link1             = #Episodes\n| episodes1         = 4<!-- should reflect the number of episodes that contribute to the average given in the last column -->\n| start1            = {{Start date|2020|4|6}}\n| end1              = \n| startrating1      = 0.55<ref name=\"1-01\" />\n| endrating1        = \n| viewers1          = {{decimals|{{#expr:((\n                      0.545 + <!-- raw ratings data data from \"The Chosen One...Stinks\" / \"Not Another Superhero Movie\" -->\n                      0.464 + <!-- raw ratings data data from \"New Kid on Campus\" / \"The Chosen One(s)\" -->\n                      0.409 + <!-- raw ratings data data from \"Lord of the Caf\" / \"Doom for Rent\" -->\n                      0.488   <!-- raw ratings data data from \"Sorry to Father You\" / \"Race to Sploosh Mountain\" -->\n                              <!-- end of raw data; please make sure one plus sign (+) follows every number above except the last entry -->\n                      )/ 4    <!-- number of episodes in this calculation; please don't remove the )/ part as it must precede the number -->\n                      )}}|2}} <!-- displays the result to two decimal places; please don't remove/move this or change the number to show more or less decimal places -->\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"The Futon Critic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/ollies-pack/listings/|title=''Ollie's Pack'' Episode Listings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Zap2it\">{{cite web|url=https://tvschedule.zap2it.com/overview.html?programSeriesId=SH03468052&tabName=guide&season=1|title=''Ollie's Pack'' Episode Guide|publisher=[[Zap2it]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|11933966}}\n\n[[Category:2020s animated television series]]\n[[Category:2020s children's television series]]\n[[Category:2020s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n\n{{tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| image                = \n| genre                = [[Action-comedy]]\n| creator              = {{plainlist |\n* Pedro Eboli\n* Graham Peterson\n}}\n| based_on             = <!-- {{based on|work|author}} -->\n| director             = Adrian Thatcher\n| developer            = Mark Satterthwaite\n| starring             = \n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| composer             = \n| country              = \n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1<!-- increment when new season begins -->\n| num_episodes         = 5<!-- increment when new episode airs -->\n| list_episodes        = \n| executive_producer   = {{plainlist |\n* Scott Dyer\n* Pam Westman\n* Graham Peterson\n* Pedro Eboli\n}}\n| producer             = Kristen Hudecki\n| cinematography       = \n| runtime              = \n| company              = [[Nelvana]]\n| network              = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[720p]]\n| audio_format         = [[5.1 surround sound]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2020|4|6}}\n| last_aired           = present\n| website              = https://www.nick.com/shows/ollies-pack\n}}\n\n'''''Ollie's Pack''''' is an [[animated]] [[action-comedy]] television series created by Pedro Eboli and Graham Peterson that premiered on [[Nickelodeon]] on April 6, 2020.\n\n==Characters==\n* Ollie (voiced by James Hartnett)<ref name=\"Futon Critic press\" />\n* Cleo (voiced by Ana Sani)<ref name=\"Futon Critic press\" />\n* Bernie (voiced by [[David Berni]])<ref name=\"Futon Critic press\" />\n\n== Production ==\nOn March 2, 2020, [[Nickelodeon]] announced that the series will premiere in April 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1234569750224818181|title=Ready to see what's inside Ollie's Pack? \ud83c\udf92 Catch the premiere this April!|user=Nickelodeon|author=Nickelodeon|author-link=Nickelodeon|date=March 2, 2020|access-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref> Pedro Eboli and Graham Peterson created the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/creatures-in-a-backpack-the-charming-world-of-ollies-pack/|title=Creatures in a Backpack: The Charming World of ''Ollie's Pack''|work=[[Animation Magazine]]|author=Ramin Zahed|date=March 19, 2020|access-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref> The 26-episode [[action-comedy]] series is produced by [[Nelvana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corusent.com/properties/ollies-pack/|title=''Ollie's Pack''|publisher=[[Corus Entertainment]]|access-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref> On March 30, 2020, it was announced that the series will premiere on April 6, 2020.<ref name=\"Futon Critic press\">{{cite press release|title=Nickelodeon Ventures Into the Monsterverse in Original Animated Series ''Ollie's Pack'', Premiering Monday, April 6 at 4:00 P.M. (ET/PT)|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2020/03/30/nickelodeon-ventures-into-the-monsterverse-in-original-animated-series-ollies-pack-premiering-monday-april-6-at-400-pm-et-pt-93204/20200330nickelodeon01/|publisher=[[Nickelodeon]]|via=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Episode table\n| background      = #F46D25\n| overall         = \n| title           = \n| titleR          = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it\" />\n| director        = \n| writer          = \n| airdate         = \n| airdateR        = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it\" />\n| prodcode        = \n| prodcodeR       = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" />\n| viewers         = \n| country         = U.S.\n| episodes        = \n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = The Chosen One...Stinks\" / \"Not Another Superhero Movie\n| DirectedBy      = Adrian Thatcher\n| WrittenBy       = Aaron Eves / Jeff Sager\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|6}}\n| ProdCode        = 103\n| Viewers         = 0.55<ref name=\"1-01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzda