roopa", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProduction:Tense updating", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ollie%27s_Pack"}
{"title_page": "Pyaar Vali Love Story", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Pyaar Vali Love Story\n| image          = pyaar_vali_love_story_poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Sanjay Jadhav]]\n| producer       = Utpal Acharya<br>Inder Raj Kapoor <br>Rekha Joshi\n| writer         = [[Sanjay Jadhav]]<br /> Aashish Pathre\n| starring       = [[Swwapnil Joshi]]<br /> [[Sai Tamhankar]]<br /> [[Urmila Kanitkar]]<br /> [[Sameer Dharmadhikari]]<br/> [[Upendra Limaye]]\n| music          = Pankaj Padghan, [[Amitraj]] and [[Samir Saptiskar]]\n| cinematography = [[Sanjay Jadhav]]\n| editing        = [[Apurva Motiwale]]<br />Ashish Mhatre\n| studio         = Cinema Company India Pvt Ltd<br/>Dreaming 24/7 Productions<br/>STV Network & Suvidesh films<ref>{{cite av media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O_9lxiqXogU |title=Pyaar Vali Love Story - Official -Teaser - Swaapnil Joshi - Sai Tamhankar - Sanjay Jadhav |date=8 July 2014 |publisher= |accessdate=5 April 2016 |via=YouTube}}</ref>\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2014|10|24|ref1=<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/pyaar-vali-love-story-on-october-2/ |title=Pyaar Vali Love Story on October 2 |date=11 April 2014 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref> }}\n| runtime        = 133 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Marathi\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|7.5|C }}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/monetary-boost-giving-marathi-cinema-a-new-lease-of-life/15648157 |title=Monetary boost giving Marathi cinema a new lease of life? - entertainment |publisher=Mid-day.com |date=2014-10-07 |accessdate=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|11.5|C }} (Lifetime)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/mam/marketing/gseams-aspires-to-one-stop-shop-for-marathi-film-industry-150608 |title=Indian Television Dot Com - GSEAMS aspires to be one-stop-shop for Marathi film industry |date=8 June 2015 |work=Indian Television Dot Com |accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Pyaar Vali Love Story''''' ('''Marathi''' :\u092a\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0930 \u0935\u093e\u0932\u0940 Love Story) is a Marathi language film directed and written by [[Sanjay Jadhav]] which released in theatres on 24 October 2014, on the occasion of [[Diwali]].<ref name=\"express1\">(8 Sept 2014). [http://m.indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/entertainment-others/marathi-films-will-enter-100-cr-club-in-three-years-sanjay-jadhav/2159766/ Marathi films will enter '100 cr club' in three years: Sanjay Jadhav], ''Indian Express''</ref>\n\nStarring [[Swwapnil Joshi]] and [[Sai Tamhankar]] in the lead roles, it also stars [[Upendra Limaye]], [[Urmila Kanetkar]]-Kothare, [[Sameer Dharmadhikari]], [[Nagesh Bhosale]] and others. The plot of the film is set in the 1990s. The film was one of the most awaited [[Marathi language|Marathi]] film<ref name=\"times1\">Deshmukh, Gayatri (3 February 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/Swwapnil-Sais-Pyaarwali-Love-Story/articleshow/29811286.cms Swwapnil-Sai's Pyaarwali Love Story], ''[[The Times of India]]''</ref><ref name=\"videostory1\">(19 April 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/regional/marathi/Pyar-Vali-Love-Story-On-location/videoshow/33956240.cms Pyar Vali Love Story: On location], ''[[The Times of India]]'' (video story)</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n''Pyar Vali Love Story'' presents stories of two lovers, who were of opposite religion. A story of two friends-Kadar and Pashya. Where Pashya's brother Amar loves Kadar's sister Aliya. Things take turn, after murder of Inspector Alam. And how Amar and Aliya face hurdles in their love story because of opposite religions and also when their brothers became enemy of each other.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Swwapnil Joshi]] as Amar\n* [[Sai Tamhankar]] as Aliya\n* [[Urmila Kanitkar]] as Nandini\n* [[Upendra Limaye]] as Kadar\n* [[Sameer Dharmadhikari]] as Pashya\n* [[Nagesh Bhosale]]\n* [[Chinmay Mandlekar]] as Inspector Alam\n* [[Jitendra Joshi]], \n* Sushant Shelar, [[Adarsh Shinde]] in a song \"Jahan Jaau\"\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! No. !! Title !! Singer(s) \n|-\n| 1 || Zara Zara || [[Javed Ali]] & Sayali Pankaj\n|-\n| 2 || Aali Lahar || [[Ajit Parab]] & Sayali Pankaj\n|-\n| 3 || Shutter Ka Tala || Rohit Raut, [[Amitraj]] & Pankaj Padghan\n|- \n| 4 || Zara Zara (Female) || Sayali Pankaj\n|-\n| 5 || Zara Zara (Male) || [[Javed Ali]] \n|-\n| 6 || Jahan Jaaun Tujhe Paaun|| [[Adarsh Shinde]], [[Divya Kumar (singer)|Divya Kumar]] & [[Ronkini]]\n|-\n| 7 || Baawari|| Jaideep Bagwadkar, Anandi Joshi & Sandeep Patil\n|-\n| 8 || Zara Zara (Unplugged) || [[Javed Ali]] & Sayali Pankaj\n|}\n\n==Box office==\nThe movie collected around {{INRConvert|1.15|c}} on first day, {{INRConvert|1.05|c}} on second day and {{INRConvert|1.30|c}} on third day, collecting {{INRConvert|3.50|c}} in its opening weekend. It fared well on weekdays at the box office, and collected around {{INRConvert|11|c}} nett. in 2 weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficecapsule.com/collection/1st-Weekend-Box-Office-Collection-Of-PYAAR-VALI-LOVE-STORY-3071}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4145848|Pyar Vali Love Story}}\n* {{Facebook|PyaarWaliLoveStoryFilm}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:Marathi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Pyaar Vali Love Story\n| image          = pyaar_vali_love_story_poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Sanjay Jadhav]]\n| producer       = Utpal Acharya<br>Inder Raj Kapoor <br>Rekha Joshi\n| writer         = [[Sanjay Jadhav]]<br /> Aashish Pathre\n| starring       = [[Swwapnil J