 Sept 2014). [http://m.indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/entertainment-others/marathi-films-will-enter-100-cr-club-in-three-years-sanjay-jadhav/2159766/ Marathi films will enter '100 cr club' in three years: Sanjay Jadhav], ''Indian Express''</ref>\n\nStarring [[Swwapnil Joshi]] and [[Sai Tamhankar]] in the lead roles, it also stars [[Upendra Limaye]], [[Urmila Kanetkar]]-Kothare, [[Sameer Dharmadhikari]], [[Nagesh Bhosale]] and others. The plot of the film is set in the 1990s. The film was one of the most awaited [[Marathi language|Marathi]] film<ref name=\"times1\">Deshmukh, Gayatri (3 February 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/Swwapnil-Sais-Pyaarwali-Love-Story/articleshow/29811286.cms Swwapnil-Sai's Pyaarwali Love Story], ''[[The Times of India]]''</ref><ref name=\"videostory1\">(19 April 2014). [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/regional/marathi/Pyar-Vali-Love-Story-On-location/videoshow/33956240.cms Pyar Vali Love Story: On location], ''[[The Times of India]]'' (video story)</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n''Pyar Vali Love Story'' presents stories of two lovers, who were of opposite religion. A story of two friends-Kadar and Pashya. Where Pashya's brother Amar loves Kadar's sister Aliya. Things take turn, after murder of Inspector Alam. And how Amar and Aliya face hurdles in their love story because of opposite religions and also when their brothers became enemy of each other.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Swwapnil Joshi]] as Amar\n* [[Sai Tamhankar]] as Aliya\n* [[Urmila Kanitkar]] as Nandini\n* [[Upendra Limaye]] as Kadar\n* [[Sameer Dharmadhikari]] as Pashya\n* [[Nagesh Bhosale]]\n* [[Chinmay Mandlekar]] as Inspector Alam\n* [[Jitendra Joshi]], \n* Sushant Shelar, [[Adarsh Shinde]] in a song \"Jahan Jaau\"\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! No. !! Title !! Singer(s) \n|-\n| 1 || Zara Zara || [[Javed Ali]] & Sayali Pankaj\n|-\n| 2 || Aali Lahar || [[Ajit Parab]] & Sayali Pankaj\n|-\n| 3 || Shutter Ka